    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "In its heyday, Glasco boasted more than six brick factories, a ferry, a school, churches, and several saloons.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glasco%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Bricks from Glasco were barge‑loaded down the Hudson to build cities across America.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        23
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glasco%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The historic Glasco Turnpike still winds past stone walls, farmland, and woodland, offering a scenic drive through the Catskills.",
